---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Maldives Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/maldives/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Thailand for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/thailand' },
  { title: 'Sri Lanka for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/sri-lanka' },
  { title: 'UAE for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/uae' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'maldivesFit', header: 'Maldives Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MVR$7,750-11,070/mo', maldivesFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MVR$9,075-12,960/mo', maldivesFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MVR$6,970-9,950/mo', maldivesFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MVR$6,475-9,245/mo', maldivesFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local (Dhivehi, Allied)', entryAge: 'Varies', renewal: 'Annual', monthlyFrom: 'MVR$2,000-4,000/mo', maldivesFit: 'Basic' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'MVR$6,970-11,070', annual: 'MVR$83,640-132,840' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'MVR$9,560-14,770', annual: 'MVR$114,720-177,240' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'MVR$12,875-19,845', annual: 'MVR$154,500-238,140' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital (Male)', monthly: 'MVR$1,500-4,000/visit', annual: 'Per incident' },
  { category: 'Medical Evacuation', monthly: 'N/A', annual: 'MVR$500,000-1,500,000' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Maldives 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Maldives. Island paradise, luxury resorts, limited healthcare, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Maldives"
  subheadline="The Maldives offers stunning island paradise, crystal waters, luxury resorts, and tropical beauty—but severely limited healthcare makes comprehensive insurance non-negotiable for seniors."
  heroImage="/images/countries/maldives-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Maldives</h2>
  <p>
    The Maldives offers unparalleled island beauty—crystal clear waters, white sand beaches, luxury overwater bungalows, and year-round tropical climate. For wealthy retirees seeking ultimate paradise and willing to accept severe healthcare limitations, the Maldives delivers unmatched beauty.
  </p>

  <p>
    Male is the capital with most services and only real hospital. Hulhumale is planned city extension. Resort islands offer luxury but minimal healthcare (basic first aid). Local islands provide cheaper living but even less healthcare. Most long-term residents stay near Male for hospital access.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Very limited; evacuation essential</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Dhivehi; English widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> MVR$30,000-80,000/month (~$2,000-5,200 USD); expensive</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical; warm year-round; monsoon seasons</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Paradise islands; Islamic; tourism-focused</li>
      <li><strong>Healthcare Reality:</strong> Not suitable for complex medical needs</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Maldives Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Maldives healthcare is very limited—Indira Gandhi Memorial Hospital (IGMH) in Male is the main facility. ADK Hospital and Tree Top Hospital are private options. Most specialists unavailable locally. Complex conditions require evacuation to Sri Lanka, Singapore, or India. Resorts have only basic first aid.
  </p>

  <p>
    Medical evacuation is common reality for any serious condition. Sri Lanka (1.5-hour flight) and Singapore (4 hours) are usual destinations. Insurance with robust evacuation coverage is absolutely essential. This is not a destination for those with complex ongoing medical needs.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Critical Healthcare Warning</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      The Maldives cannot treat most serious conditions locally. Medical evacuation to Sri Lanka or Singapore is common necessity. Seniors with cardiac conditions, cancer, or other complex needs should carefully consider whether Maldives is appropriate. Evacuation insurance is non-negotiable.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Maldives has limited long-term options:
  </p>

  <h3>Tourist Visa</h3>
  <p>
    30 days on arrival for most nationalities. Extensions to 90 days possible. Many use visa runs for extended stays.
  </p>

  <h3>Work Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For employed by Maldivian company. Not typical retirement route but some semi-retired professionals use this.
  </p>

  <h3>Business Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For those with business interests. Various categories and requirements.
  </p>

  <h3>Special Permission</h3>
  <p>
    Long-term residence requires special immigration permission. Not straightforward for retirees.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Maldives:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> COVID rules have varied; verify current requirements</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> Comprehensive international coverage essential</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Non-negotiable minimum $500,000+</li>
    <li><strong>Regional access:</strong> Singapore, Sri Lanka, India coverage critical</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Maldives</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Comprehensive international insurance with robust evacuation coverage ($500,000+ minimum) is absolutely essential. Include Singapore, Sri Lanka, and India for treatment. This is not where to economize. Consider whether Maldives is appropriate for your health profile before committing.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Maldives, premium coverage with strong evacuation essential:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Maldives</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Asia network, excellent evacuation</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Singapore network:</strong> Premier regional medical hub</li>
    <li><strong>Don't economize:</strong> This is not where to save money</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare premium coverage with strong Asia evacuation.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Maldives (MVR ~15.4 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Don't cut evacuation:</strong> This is not where to save</li>
    <li><strong>Singapore network:</strong> Use designated hospitals for better rates</li>
    <li><strong>Preventive care:</strong> Stay healthy; minimize complex needs</li>
    <li><strong>Honest assessment:</strong> Consider if Maldives suits your health profile</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Healthy Wealthy American, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $8,000/month income. Excellent health. Near Male.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global premium with maximum evacuation.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~MVR$9,000/month (~$585). Paradise living; Singapore backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Resort Manager, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £5,000/month income. Work permit. Resort island.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global comprehensive with UK coverage for visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~MVR$11,000/month (~$715). Island work; global security.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Indian Ocean Enthusiast, 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $6,000/month income. Split time Maldives/Singapore. Hulhumale.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with Asia focus. Singapore for care.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~MVR$12,500/month (~$810). Strategic positioning; healthcare access.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Maldives healthcare really that limited?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—Maldives cannot treat most serious conditions locally. Heart attacks, strokes, cancer require evacuation. Even routine surgery often sends patients to Sri Lanka or India. Beautiful for healthy people; challenging for those with medical needs.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I actually retire to Maldives?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Difficult—no retirement visa. Most use tourist visa rotations, work permits, or business arrangements. Long-term residence requires special permission. Not straightforward for permanent retirement compared to Thailand or Portugal.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Maldives expensive?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—almost everything is imported. Resort island living is luxury-priced. Male/Hulhumale is expensive for what you get. Budget MVR$30,000-80,000/month minimum. Not a budget retirement destination; beauty comes at premium.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about climate change and sea levels?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Genuine concern—Maldives is world's lowest-lying country. Sea level rise is existential threat. Government actively addressing through land reclamation and international advocacy. Long-term viability is legitimate consideration for permanent retirement.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Maldives coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Maldives authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
